In [529]:
null_col=[]
for i,j in enumerate(df.columns):
    if df.isnull().sum()[i]>0:
        df[j].fillna(df[j].median(),inplace=True)
        null_col.append(j)
    else:
        pass

outlier_col=[]
col=['prod_class','prod_dur','tmp_1','tmp_2','tmp_3','tmp_4','tmp_5','tmp_6','tmp_7','rev_prob']
for i in col:
    f, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(17,7))
    sns.boxplot(x = i, data=df,  orient='h' , ax=axes[1])
    #sns.set(axis_bgcolor='k')
    sns.distplot(df[i],  ax=axes[0], kde_kws = {'bw' : 1})
    axes[0].set_title('Distribution plot of {}'.format(i))
    axes[1].set_title('Box plot of {}'.format(i))
    plt.show()
    #checking count of outliers.
    q25,q75=np.percentile(df[i],25),np.percentile(df[i],75)
    IQR=q75-q25
    Threshold=IQR*1.5
    lower,upper=q25-Threshold,q75+Threshold
    Outliers=[i for i in df[i] if i < lower or i > upper]
    if len(Outliers)>0:
        outlier_col.append(i)    
    print('{} Total Number of outliers in {}: {}'.format('\033[1m',i,len(Outliers)))

Statistical Tests¶

Do Revenue of Customer who is special differ significantly from the people who don't?¶

In [558]:
plt.figure(figsize=(15,7))
sns.boxplot(x='is_special', y='rev_prob', data= df)
plt.show()

Graph shows two means are nearly equal.

H0:Revenue of Special and Non-Special customers are same

H1:Revenue of Special and Non-Special customers are not same

T-Test

In [559]:
from scipy.stats import  ttest_ind
import scipy.stats as stats
In [560]:
x = np.array(df[df.is_special == 1.0].rev_prob) 
y = np.array(df[df.is_special == 0.0].rev_prob)
t, p_value  = stats.ttest_ind(x,y, axis = 0) 
print('P_Value:', p_value)

if p_value < 0.05:  # Setting our significance level at 5%
    print('Rejecting Null Hypothesis.Revenue of Special and Non-Special customers are not same')
else:
    print('Fail to Reject Null Hypothesis.Revenue of Special and Non-Special customers are same')

P_Value: 0.6680868336778332
Fail to Reject Null Hypothesis.Revenue of Special and Non-Special customers are same

There is no significant difference in revenue for special and non-special customer.

Do Revenue of Customer of different class of os_class differ significantly?¶

H0:No of os_class does not affects revenue

H1:No of os_class affects revenue

Anova Test

In [561]:
x = np.array(df[df.os_class == 1].rev_prob) 
y = np.array(df[df.os_class == 2].rev_prob)
z = np.array(df[df.os_class == 3].rev_prob)
f_stats,p_value=stats.f_oneway(x,y,z)
print('F_stats:',f_stats)
print('p_value:',p_value)
if p_value < 0.05:  # Setting our significance level at 5%
    print('Rejecting Null Hypothesis.No of os_class  affects revenue')
else:
    print('Fail to Reject Null Hypothesis.No of os_class does not affects revenue')

F_stats: 0.7840525026836408
p_value: 0.4566252676339154
Fail to Reject Null Hypothesis.No of os_class does not affects revenue

Os_class does not significantly affecting Revenue

Model Building¶

In [574]:
def regression(X, Y, reg, param_grid, test_size=0.20):
    
    X_train, X_test, Y_train, Y_test = train_test_split(X, Y, test_size=test_size, random_state=42)
      
    
    reg = RandomizedSearchCV(reg,parameters, cv = 10,refit = True)
    reg.fit(X_train, Y_train)     

    return X_train, X_test, Y_train, Y_test, reg
In [575]:
def evaluation_metrics(X_train, X_test, Y_train, Y_test, reg):
    Y_pred_train = reg.best_estimator_.predict(X_train)
    Y_pred_test = reg.best_estimator_.predict(X_test)
    
    print("Best Parameters:",reg.best_params_)
    print('\n')
    print("Mean cross-validated score of the best_estimator : ", reg.best_score_) 
    print('\n')
    MAE_train = metrics.mean_absolute_error(Y_train, Y_pred_train)
    MAE_test = metrics.mean_absolute_error(Y_test, Y_pred_test)
    print('MAE for training set is {}'.format(MAE_train))
    print('MAE for test set is {}'.format(MAE_test))
    print('\n')

OLS Model With Forward Selection.¶

In [581]:
import statsmodels.formula.api as smf

def forward_selected(data, response):
    """Linear model designed by forward selection.

    Parameters:
    -----------
    data : pandas DataFrame with all possible predictors and response

    response: string, name of response column in data

    Returns:
    --------
    model: an "optimal" fitted statsmodels linear model
           with an intercept
           selected by forward selection
           evaluated by adjusted R-squared
    """
    remaining = set(data.columns)
    remaining.remove(response)
    selected = []
    current_score, best_new_score = 0.0, 0.0
    while remaining and current_score == best_new_score:
        scores_with_candidates = []
        for candidate in remaining:
            formula = "{} ~ {} + 1".format(response,
                                           ' + '.join(selected + [candidate]))
            score = smf.ols(formula, data).fit().rsquared_adj
            scores_with_candidates.append((score, candidate))
        scores_with_candidates.sort()
        best_new_score, best_candidate = scores_with_candidates.pop()
        if current_score < best_new_score:
            remaining.remove(best_candidate)
            selected.append(best_candidate)
            current_score = best_new_score
    formula = "{} ~ {} + 1".format(response,
                                   ' + '.join(selected))
    model = smf.ols(formula, data).fit()
    return model

Making all preprocessings steps into one function

In [516]:
def pre_process(df):
    df.drop('date',axis=1,inplace=True)
    null_col=[]
    #missing value
    for i,j in enumerate(df.columns):
        if df.isnull().sum()[i]>0:
            df[j].fillna(df[j].median(),inplace=True)
            null_col.append(j)
        else:
            pass
    #setting index    
    df.set_index(['sess_id'],inplace=True)
    #converting date
    #df['date']=pd.to_datetime(df['date'])
    #is_special
    df['is_special'].values[df['is_special'] > 0.5] = 1
    df['is_special'].values[df['is_special'] < 0.5] = 0
    #os_class
    df['os_class'].values[df['os_class'] > 3] = 3
    #int_brws
    df['int_brws'].values[df['int_brws'] > 2] = 3
    #traffic class
    df['traffic_class'].values[df['traffic_class'] > 3] = 4
    #region
    df['region'].values[df['region'] > 3] = 4
    #log tranformation
    col=['prod_class','prod_dur','tmp_1','tmp_2','tmp_3','tmp_4','tmp_5','tmp_6','tmp_7']
    for i in col:
        df[i] = np.log(df[i])
    df = df.replace([np.inf, -np.inf, -0], 0)
    #encoding
    df['vis_type']=labelencoder.fit_transform(df['vis_type'])
    #changing datatypes
    df['is_special']=df['is_special'].astype('category') 
    df['os_class']=df['os_class'].astype('category') 
    df['region']=df['region'].astype('category') 
    df['traffic_class']=df['traffic_class'].astype('category') 
    df['vis_type']=df['vis_type'].astype('category') 
    df['is_weekend']=df['is_weekend'].astype('category') 
    df['int_brws']=df['int_brws'].astype('category') 
    #statistical insignificant column
    drop_cat_col=['region','int_brws','os_class','is_special']
    df.drop(drop_cat_col,axis=1,inplace=True)
    return df
